commit 20ee1e54ac0f21c0cedb7ed1fd3427b4d65c962a
Author: Jason Cohen <jcohen@nvidia.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 6 18:27:03 2022 -0500

    Breaking change: Rename domain-templated classes and functions to consistently use preferred pattern

    Previously only scoped_range and unique_range used the pattern of "scoped_range" for the global domain and "scoped_range_in<D>" for domain D.  The others (mark, start/end_range, named_category, registered_string) used "mark<>" for the global domain and "mark<D>" for domain D.  This change converts all of these to consistently follow the scoped_range pattern, so non-library clients who aren't using domains don't have to remember the <> everywhere.

    This change also updates the doxygen comments to use the new names, and a handful of other typo fixes ("nvxt", "variadiac").  Example code was fixed to use "auto&" instead of "auto" for get() functions that return references, and the resulting variables were renamed if they had the same name as the tag type to avoid confusion.

    Testing passes all previous cases, but new tests written to cover named_category and registered_string in the global domain fail on VS2015.  These will be addressed in the next commit.
